From d439702d794d348520a1815c9f0c1458c2671c9e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: eWloYW8 <3171132517@qq.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 10:16:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] sunxi: radxa-cubie-a5e: select DRAM profile by detected size

Radxa ships separate Cubie A5E DRAM parameter sets. The 1GB LPDDR4 variant uses cubie_a5e/sys_config.fex, while the larger LPDDR4x variants use cubie_a5e/sys_config_ddr_2GB.fex.

The common A523 driver already performs an initial low-speed DRAM pass to detect rank, bus width and size, then reinitializes DRAM with the final clock and timing. Keep that first pass generic, but after detection choose the Radxa profile for the final initialization:

  - <= 1024 MiB: cubie_a5e/sys_config.fex

  - >  1024 MiB: cubie_a5e/sys_config_ddr_2GB.fex

Some LPDDR4 mode registers are currently hard-coded in the timing and PHY initialization paths, so thread them through struct dram_config before selecting the Cubie A5E profile. Also use the selected MR2 during write leveling and keep the controller timing bucket consistent with the selected MR1/MR2 values.

Signed-off-by: eWloYW8 <3171132517@qq.com>
